briefTitle: Safety and Immunogenicity Study of V503 (GARDASIL™9, 9vHPV Vaccine) Administered to 9- to 26-Year-Old Females and Males in Vietnam (V503-017)
officialTitle: A Phase III Open-label Safety and Immunogenicity Study of GARDASIL™9 Administered to 9- to 26-Year-Old Females and Males in Vietnam
summary: This study will evaluate the safety and immunogenicity of V503 (GARDASIL™9, 9vHPV vaccine) administered to 9- to 26-year-old females and males in Vietnam. The study hypothesis states that V503 induces acceptable anti-human papillomavirus (HPV) 6, 11, 16, 18, 31, 33, 45, 52, and 58 seroconversion at 4 weeks postdose 3.

primaryOutcome.measure: Seroconversion Percentages to HPV Types 6, 11, 16, 18, 31, 33, 45, 52, and 58 at Month 7
